<L>__{interior kenny's office night}
<A>__{kenny rubs his eyes, listens to his phone and the woman's voice at the other end. it's his wife.}
<C>__{helen }
<D>__{when are you going to be home?}
<C>__{kenny}
<D>__{i don't know, helen. i want you to keep the kids close tomorrow. leave the t.v. on, sleep with it on in the bedroom until i tell you you can turn it off.}
<C>__{helen }
<D>__{what's happened?}
<C>__{kenny}
<D>__{nothing. nothing you don't know about. tomorrow's the big day. just have the car ready to go if i call or if the civil defense warning comes on.}
<C>__{helen }
<D>__{what happens to you? i'm not leaving without you.}
<C>__{kenny}
<D>__{i will be evacuated with the president.}
<A>__{a long silence on the other end of the line.}
<C>__{helen }
<D>__{great. so while you're under a rock somewhere with the president, what am i supposed to do with your five children?}
<A>__{and to that, there is no answer. a beat, and it's all kenny can promise:}
<C>__{kenny}
<D>__{i will find you. but we're not going to let it come to that. i promise.}
